FBIS4-4303 "dreas062_c_94006" FBIS-EAS-94-062 Daily Report 28 Mar 1994 North Korea Radio Reports ROK Premier's Public Alert Order Radio Reports ROK Premier's Public Alert Order SK3103002294 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 1300 GMT 28 Mar 94 SK3103002294 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 1300 GMT 28 Mar 94 Korean BFN [Text] The puppet prime minister showed up at the "Seoul City Police Office" on March 27 and ordered it to "maintain a perfect public peace and alert posture", according to a radio report from Seoul. On March 26, while making a round of frontline units of the puppet Army, he incited war fever for a northward invasion, crying for a flawless "posture for countermove". Facts that have been revealed show that the South Korean puppets are getting more frenzied with the passage of time in driving North-South relations to a phase of confrontation and war [taekyolgwa chonjaeng kungmyon].
